  "prompt": "I'm doing my first pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3. What stats do I need to build on to be most effective?",
  "response": "Okay, a Pyromancer build in Dark Souls 3 is a lot of fun and can be very powerful. Here's a breakdown of the stats you should focus on, why they're important, and some suggested early-game stat allocation:\n\n**Core Stats:**\n\n*   **Intelligence (INT) and Faith (FTH):** These are the *most* important stats for a Pyromancer. Pyromancies scale with *both* Intelligence and Faith. You want to level these roughly equally. The \"soft cap\" for scaling is 40/40, and the hard cap is 60/60. Going beyond 40/40 gives diminishing returns, but is still worth it if you have levels to spare.\n\n*   **Attunement (ATT):** This determines your FP (Focus Points) and how many attunement slots you have. FP is used to cast pyromancies. Attunement slots let you equip more pyromancies at once. The amount of FP gained per level diminishes after 30, so that's a good place to stop and evaluate your needs. At least 30 ATT is recommended, some players go for 35, 40 or even higher depending on their playstyle.\n    *   **For early game, you want around 18 ATT for three slots.** Then, you can aim for 24 (4 slots) or 30 (5 slots).\n\n**Secondary/Utility Stats:**\n\n*   **Vigor (VIG):** Determines your HP. You need enough to survive a few hits, especially in PvE. Aim for at least 27 VIG early on, and eventually get this to 35-40+. Survival is key to any build.\n\n*   **Endurance (END):** Determines your stamina. Stamina is used for attacking, dodging, and blocking. You'll need enough to comfortably perform your attacks and dodges. Aim for at least 20 END early on, and scale it up to 25-30+ as you progress.\n\n*   **Vitality (VIT):** Determines your equip load. You need enough to wear the armor you want without being over-encumbered (stay below 70% equip load for normal rolling). Pyromancers don't generally need heavy armor, but you'll want some to protect you, so raise this as needed to support your chosen gear. The Prisoner's Chain is also incredibly useful for increasing your Equip Load (as well as Vigor and Endurance).\n\n*   **Dexterity (DEX):**  While not strictly necessary, some Pyromancies *do* have slightly faster cast speed with higher Dexterity, and it increases the cast speed of spells up to 50 DEX. This is a good stat to invest in if you have points left over after meeting your core requirements, or if you want to use some Dexterity-scaling weapons like katanas or rapiers.\n\n*   **Strength (STR):**  Only raise this enough to meet the minimum requirements for any weapons you want to use. Some Pyromancer builds use the Longsword or other weapons with moderate STR requirements.\n\n*   **Luck (LCK):** Don't invest in this stat unless you're specifically building a Luck build, which is a very different playstyle. It's largely irrelevant to Pyromancy.\n\n**Prioritization:**\n\n1.  **Early Game:** Vigor, Attunement, Endurance, Intelligence, and Faith need attention first. You need enough health to survive, enough FP to cast, enough stamina to dodge and attack, and Intelligence/Faith to deal damage.\n2.  **Mid Game:** Focus on getting Intelligence/Faith to 40/40. Continue raising Vigor and Endurance as needed.\n3.  **Late Game:** You can either push Intelligence/Faith towards 60/60 for maximum scaling, or you can invest in Dexterity, Vitality, or other stats depending on your preferred playstyle.\n\n**Starting Class:**\n\n*   **Pyromancer:** This is the ideal starting class for a Pyromancer build due to its balanced starting stats and access to the Pyromancy Flame.\n    * *Note*: The starting class only really affects the early game. Eventually, with enough levels, every class can reach the same stats.\n\n**Example Early-Game Stat Allocation (Around Level 30-40):**\n\nThis is just a guideline. Adjust as you see fit based on your preferred playstyle.\n\n*   Vigor: 20-25\n*   Attunement: 18-24\n*   Endurance: 15-20\n*   Vitality: 10-15 (Enough for your starting armor and a light weapon)\n*   Strength: 10-12 (Enough for a Longsword or similar)\n*   Dexterity: 12-14 (Enough for a Longsword or similar)\n*   Intelligence: 20-25\n*   Faith: 20-25\n*   Luck: 7 (Base for Pyromancer)\n\n**Key Pyromancies to Aim For:**\n\n*   **Early Game:**\n    *   Fireball\n    *   Great Combustion\n    *   Fire Surge\n*   **Mid Game:**\n    *   Great Chaos Fire Orb\n    *   Chaos Bed Vestiges\n    *   Black Flame\n    *   Fire Whip\n*   **Late Game:**\n    *   Flame Fan\n    *   Seething Chaos\n    *   Combustion\n\n**Weapons and Rings:**\n\n*   **Weapons:**\n    *   Raw Astora Straight Sword/Longsword: Infuse with Raw early on and buff with Carthus Flame Arc to deal consistent physical damage\n    *   Lothric Knight Sword/Other Straight Sword: After you have 40/40 INT/FTH, infuse with Chaos or Dark.\n    *   Pyromancer's Parting Flame: Use this to cast offensive pyromancies because the ash effect leaves a DoT, then switch back to the normal Pyromancy Flame for the passive damage boosts.\n\n*   **Rings:**\n    *   Great Swamp Ring: Boosts Pyromancy damage.\n    *   Witch's Ring: Boosts Pyromancy damage.\n    *   Sage Ring: Increases casting speed (Stack this with Dexterity to achieve max cast speed)\n    *   Fire Clutch Ring: Increases Fire damage, but reduces physical absorption. Use with caution! Good for boss fights.\n    *   Prisoner's Chain: Increases Vigor, Endurance, and Vitality. This is one of the best rings in the game, period.\n    *   Chloranthy Ring: Increases stamina recovery speed.\n    *   Ring of Favor: Increases HP, stamina, and equip load.\n    *   Life Ring: Increases HP.\n\n**General Tips:**\n\n*   **Infusion:** Raw weapons with Carthus Flame Arc early on are excellent. Later, use Chaos or Dark infusions on your weapons once you have high INT/FTH.\n*   **Experiment:** Try out different pyromancies and find the ones that suit your playstyle. Some are better for PvE, others for PvP.\n*   **Don't Rely Solely on Fire:** Some enemies are resistant or immune to fire. Have a backup plan, such as the Dark Pyromancies, or a weapon with physical damage.\n*   **Estus Allocation:** Early on, focus on Ashen Estus Flasks (FP recovery) to use more pyromancies. Later, you can adjust your allocation to balance healing and FP recovery.\n*   **Practice Free Aiming:** Some pyromancies are easier to land when you free aim them.\n\nHave fun burning your enemies to a crisp!\n",
